race.comment: KIDDING ME (9) was solid first-up as the odds-on favourite at this track, beaten 1.2L when just feeling the pinch late. She'll be better for that effort and Faithfull remaining in the saddle is a positive sign. Can improve on the fresh effort and she'll prove very hard to run down. DIXIE PRINCESS (5) hasn't been far away her past couple and steps up to 1200m again today. She's a long-time maiden, though she has early speed and her recent form stacks right up. Can put her best foot forward once again. IN SITU (11) is on debut today and won his latest trial in good fashion when moving to the Stokes barn. The wide draw is a niggle, but this looks a suitable race on debut. Can feature in the finish. SUMMER MOOD (6) can make an impact first-up. CHINESE DENTIST (1) gets the blinkers on first time today and the better draw suits. Not out of this.
